               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1225" notBefore="1200">13th century,
                        first quarter; fols. 1–3, 14th century</origDate>
                     <origPlace cert="low">
                        <country key="place_7002445">English</country>, <settlement
                           key="place_7010823">Ramsey</settlement>
                        (?)<!--ORIGINAL: English, Ramsey (?)--></origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance><orgName role="fmo" key="org_121821230">Ramsey, Benedictine
                        Abbey</orgName>: the presence of lives of Ivo and of Ethelred and
                     Ethelbricht suggest Ramsey, as does the note on fol. 108: 'Hec qui descripsit
                     devotus quisque rescripsit Yvo sacer de te placeat dominoque tibique'. Gerard
                     Langbaine called it 'a good old book which was sometime the passional of the
                     monastery of Ramsey' (letter to Archbishop Ussher ed. Parr, Life of Ussher
                     (1686), p. 552). (<ref target="http://mlgb3.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/mlgb/book/6749/"
                        >MLGB3</ref>: evidence from locally specific contents, including obits,
                     scribbles, etc.)</provenance>
                  <provenance>At fol. 165v is added in a late 13th cent. hand 'Perlectis itaque
                     Passionalibus, legatur Vita sancti Martialis episcopi. Queratur in armario,
                     in ueteri libro spisso, &amp; paruo [then a 14th cent. hand has added:]
                     qui intitulatur Diadema Monachorum', a work by Smaragdus.</provenance>
                  <acquisition when="1601">Presented by <persName role="dnr" key="person_100183464"
                        >dr. Thomas James</persName>, first Bodley's Librarian, in
                     1601.</acquisition>

               </history>
